From a61879c132618e0eaf47718a1a26d496557bd3d7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 15:27:09 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] T3.4: Paginate admin/Members.jsx + clarify AdminDashboard
 scope
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds client-side pagination (25 per page) to admin/Members.jsx with a
server-side fetch cap of 500 records. Solves the real scaling problem:
admins scrolling through a growing member list can now navigate by
page number instead of waiting for an unbounded fetch and scrolling.

Scope decision: AdminDashboard's User.list() was NOT paginated in this
PR. Upfront analysis showed that fetch is used for:
  - Role breakdown charts (needs all records)
  - Total member counts (needs all records)
  - Pending-user synthetic-app derivation (needs all records)

These are aggregation concerns, not a list-scrolling problem.
Pagination wouldn't help — you can't page #2 of 'total TC count'.
The proper fix is a server-side stats endpoint returning aggregates
only, which requires a custom Base44 function (multi-day work,
tracked separately). Updated the code comment to explain this.

Implementation details for Members.jsx pagination:

- FETCH_CAP = 500: server-side hard ceiling. Base44's SDK in this
  codebase doesn't expose offset/cursor primitives, so true server-
  side pagination isn't available. Beta scale (<500 members) is
  covered; past that, we need the Base44 primitives upgrade.

- PAGE_SIZE = 25: standard admin table ergonomics. Shown in
  'Showing X-Y of Z (filtered from M total)' counter at the footer.

- Approaching-cap banner: when member count reaches FETCH_CAP - 20,
  a visible banner warns admins they're seeing a truncated list and
  points at the follow-up work.

- computePageNumbers helper: builds a smart page-number window with
  ellipses for large totals. Verified via manual test:
    compute(3, 5)   -> [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]          (no ellipsis below 8 pages)
    compute(1, 20)  -> [1, 2, '...', 20]
    compute(10, 20) -> [1, '...', 9, 10, 11, '...', 20]
    compute(20, 20) -> [1, '...', 19, 20]

- Reset-to-page-1 on search/filter change via useEffect, so admins
  don't land on page 5 when the new filter has 2 pages.

- currentPage is clamped to Math.min(page, totalPages) so deleting
  users doesn't leave the admin stuck on an empty page.

- Pagination footer only renders when filtered.length > PAGE_SIZE.
  Single-page results don't need the nav clutter.

- filtered list is now memoized (useMemo) — previously recalculated
  on every render. Small perf win.

Custom nav instead of shadcn Pagination primitive:
  Shadcn's Pagination uses <a> tags meant for server-side routing.
  For client-side page changes, <button> is the semantically correct
  element. Custom minimal implementation (~30 lines) with proper
  button semantics, aria-label, aria-current, and keyboard/screen
  reader support.

Files (2):
  - src/pages/admin/Members.jsx (+133/-11)
  - src/pages/dashboard/AdminDashboard.jsx (+8/-0) -- comment only

Verification:
  - npm run lint: 0 errors (full codebase)
  - Scoped lint: 0 errors, 3 pre-existing warnings (unused vars)
  - npm run build: succeeds
  - computePageNumbers helper verified via Node for edge cases
